<h3>Travel By Air</h3>
<h4>For Persons with Visual Impairments</h4>
<ul>
<li>The Indian Airlines Corporation allows 50 percent concessional fare to persons with visual impairments on one-way trips or a single fare for a round trip journey on all domestic flights.</li> 
<li>Escorts traveling with a person with visual impairment are to pay the full fare.</li>
<li>The flight attendant will look after the person with visual impairment not accompanied by an escort.</li>
<li>This concession cannot be combined with any other concessional fare allowed by Indian Airlines.</li>
<li>For additional informational information and to download the form refer to 
<a href="http://rehabcouncil.nic.in/olink/rights_privileges.htm#travel">http://rehabcouncil.nic.in/olink/rights_privileges.htm#travel</a></li>
</ul>

<h4>For Persons with Physical Disabilities</h4>
<ul>
<li>Persons with physical disabilities (80 percent and above) can avail of the following concessions on Indian Airline flights
<ul>
<li>A 50 percent concession for an economy class INR fare or point to point fare.</li>
<li>A 50 percent concession for an INR fare applicable to foreign residents in India.</li>
</ul></li>
</ul>

